      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Empirical studies generally show that the negative impact of immigration on the wages of native-born workers is very small, especially when looking at the overall economy. While some localized or specific low-skill sectors might see minor competitive effects, the vast body of economic research does not support the notion of widespread, significant wage depression caused by immigration. Modern economies also benefit from immigrants filling gaps that domestic labor may not otherwise cover, which can boost overall productivity.",
