      "content": "The persistence of this issue in political debate often stems from a disconnect between complex economic modeling and public perception. Political messaging frequently simplifies nuanced data into easily digestible, emotionally resonant narratives, even when the underlying evidence is more complex. Furthermore, social and cultural concerns often drive the political conversation more strongly than purely economic analyses. Therefore, the debate has become less about precise labor market mechanics and more about identity and national sentiment.",
